The closure test
501 — Philosophy and theory of science
--------------------------------------------------
A framework F with state space S and evolution/ 
generation map Γ: S → S is realistically closed 
if and only if the Closure, Completeness, Causality,
Consistency conditions simultaneously hold.

                  +-----------------------+
                  |    REALISTIC CLOSURE   |
                  +-----------+-----------+
                              |
        +---------------------+---------------------+
        |                     |                     |
  [ CLOSURE ]          [ COMPLETENESS ]        [ CAUSALITY ]
  Γ(S) ⊆ S             Causes(Γ) ⊆ S           M ⇝ Γ
  No Out-of-Bounds     Zero Exogenous          Physical Substrate
  Leakage              Hidden Variables        Grounding
                               |
                        [ CONSISTENCY ]
                        Γ_t = Γ_(t+1)
                        Stationary Laws

---
A framework is reality‑mapping iff:

  Closure ∧ Completeness ∧ Causality ∧ Consistency

If any condition fails:

  ¬(Closure ∧ Completeness ∧ Causality ∧ Consistency)
  → the framework is not reality‑mapping.
---

A framework is realistically closed iff:

Closure Condition  

  ∀𝑋 ∈ State, Γ(𝑋) ∈ State
  ∀X∈S, Γ(X)∈S

Completeness Condition

  State contains all variables that affect Γ
  Causes(Γ)⊆S

Causality Condition

  Γ corresponds to a real causal mechanism
  ∃M such that M generates Γ
  M ⇝ Γ

Consistency Condition

  Γ is stable across time
  Γ_𝑡 = Γ_(𝑡+1) = Γ
  ∀t, Γt​=Γ

If any of these fail → the framework is not reality‑
mapping.

